9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 668, L.D. 1715, “RESOLUTION,
10 Proposing an Amendment to the Constitution of Maine to Amend the Appointment and
11 Confirmation Process for Certain Judicial, Civil and Military Officers”
12 Amend the resolution in that part designated "Constitution, Art. V, Part First, §8,
13 2nd ¶" in the indented paragraph in the 6th line (page 1, line 10 in L.D.) by striking out
14 the following: "vote of 2/3" and inserting the following: 'majority vote of 2/3'
15 Amend the resolution in the question in the 2nd line (page 1, line 20 in L.D.) by
16 inserting after the following: "confirm" the following: 'gubernatorial'
17 Amend the resolution in the question in the 2nd line (page 1, line 20 in L.D.) by striking
18 out the following: "2/3" and inserting the following: 'majority'
19 Amend the resolution by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
20 section number to read consecutively.
21 SUMMARY
2222 The resolution proposes to amend the Constitution of Maine to allow the Senate to
2233 confirm nominations of certain judicial, civil and military officers by a 2/3 vote.
2244 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, proposes to amend the
2255 Constitution of Maine to allow the Senate to confirm gubernatorial nominations by
2266 majority vote.
